This repo contains python scripts for conerting VASP output files
into input file for the ANETO method.
ANETO is a method for calclating the elastic self interaction 
energy for point defects calculated in a periodic cell using a 
first principles method such as VASP.
This interaction energy can be subtracted from the point defect
energy to determine the energy of the isolated defect.
Aneto can be found at http://emmanuel.clouet.free.fr/Programs/Aneto/aneto.html
and its method is details in this paper:DOI: https://doi.org/10.1103/

This repo assumes that the elastic strain was zero during the
point defect calculations, ie. only atomic positions relaxed when
a defect was inserted into a pristine supercell.

Requirements:
python 3.? (was built with python 3.12)
uv which can be installed in a conda environment with "conda install uv"

INPUTs:
config file which includes directions to the directories where the elastic 
modulus, reference supercell, and defect supercell, can be found
the elastic modulus can also be input directly, though it is recomended to 
calculate with the method used to calculate the defect energies.

a sample input can be found at "config_sample.json"

OUTPUTs:
A directory will be created and filled with files called "input_elast.##"
These are files formatted in the ANETO input file format
Please see ANETO's documentation for information on installation.

